  "prompt": "How do you factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer?",
  "response": "To factory reset an iPhone 4 without using a computer, you can do so directly from the device itself. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Back Up Your Data**: Before performing a factory reset, ensure that you back up any important data. You can use iCloud for this if your iPhone 4 is running iOS 7 or later. Go to **Settings > iCloud > Backup**, and select **Back Up Now**.\n\n2. **Open Settings**: Tap on the **Settings** app on your home screen.\n\n3. **General Settings**: Scroll down and tap on **General**.\n\n4. **Reset Option**: Scroll all the way down and tap on **Reset**.\n\n5. **Erase All Content and Settings**: Tap on **Erase All Content and Settings**. You may be asked to enter your passcode if you have one set.\n\n6. **Confirm Erase**: A warning box will appear to confirm that you want to erase your iPhone. Tap **Erase iPhone** to confirm.\n\n7. **Wait for Reset**: Your iPhone will begin the reset process, which may take a few minutes. Once completed, the iPhone will restart and display the setup screen.\n\nRemember, performing a factory reset will erase all data from your device, including settings, accounts, apps, and media, so ensure that all important data is backed up before proceeding.",
